Description. Size: 0.55–0.80 mm females ( holotype 0.75 mm). Colour: pale with diffuse pigment more concentrated in eye fields. Body long and slender (
Figs 3–4
). Dorsal chaetae smooth and pointed. SA macrochaeta on Abd IV 0.20–0.25, on Abd V 0.50–0.55 times the tergite length (
Fig 7
).

Five omma on each side of head. PAO long and narrow, 3.5 times as long as an omma, with two posterior chaetae (
Fig 10
). 2 /5,5,4 labral chaetae. Maxillary palp bifurcate with three sublobal chaetae.
